    excerpt: "University of Melbourne fees, courses & admission 2025 guide for international students. QS Rank #37, tuition from \u20b922-28 LPA, scholarships up to 100%.",
    content: "<h2>University Overview</h2><p>The University of Melbourne, founded in 1853, is Australia's second-oldest university and consistently ranks among the world's top institutions. Located in Parkville, Melbourne, it holds the <strong>QS World Ranking #37 (2025)</strong> and stands as Asia-Pacific's leading university. The campus spans 22 hectares with 50,000+ students, of which <strong>31% are international students (approximately 15,500 students)</strong>. India sends around 3,800 students annually, making it the largest source of international enrollment.</p><h2>Why Choose University of Melbourne?</h2><p>Melbourne offers <strong>world-class research opportunities</strong> with AUD $210 million in annual research income. The university boasts Nobel Prize winners and has produced leaders in medicine, law, and engineering. Notable alumni include Rupert Murdoch (media mogul), Fred Hollows (humanitarian), and Fiona Wood (inventor of spray-on skin). The university's emphasis on practical learning, industry partnerships, and global perspectives makes graduates highly competitive. It consistently ranks in top 100 for 25+ disciplines including Medicine, Engineering, Law, and Business.</p><h2>Popular Courses 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Master of Business Administration (MBA)</strong> \u2013 2 years, \u20b925-28 LPA, strong finance/consulting placement</li><li><strong>Master of Engineering (various specializations)</strong> \u2013 2 years, \u20b924-26 LPA, 94% employment within 6 months</li><li><strong>Master of Information Technology</strong> \u2013 2 years, \u20b922-24 LPA, average salary AUD $75,000</li><li><strong>Master of Laws (LLM)</strong> \u2013 1-2 years, \u20b923-25 LPA, leading law firms recruit heavily</li><li><strong>Bachelor of Science</strong> \u2013 3 years, \u20b920-22 LPA, research-focused program</li><li><strong>Master of Public Health</strong> \u2013 2 years, \u20b919-21 LPA, healthcare sector demand high</li><li><strong>Master of Analytics</strong> \u2013 2 years, \u20b925-27 LPA, tech industry recruitment strong</li></ul><h2>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>International Student Fees (per annum):</strong></p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\"><tr><td><strong>Program Level</strong></td><td><strong>USD</strong></td><td><strong>INR (approx)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Undergraduate</td><td>$32,000-38,000</td><td>\u20b926-31 LPA</td></tr><tr><td>Postgraduate (Coursework)</td><td>$28,000-45,000</td><td>\u20b923-37 LPA</td></tr><tr><td>Postgraduate (Research)</td><td>$15,000-25,000</td><td>\u20b912-20 LPA</td></tr></table><p><strong>Living Costs (Annual):</strong> \u20b912-18 LPA (AUD $2,500-3,500/month) including accommodation, food, transport. <strong>Total Annual Cost:</strong> \u20b934-49 LPA for UG, \u20b935-55 LPA for PG. Indian students can avail education loans from ICICI Bank, State Bank of India, and HDFC Bank covering 90-100% of fees.</p><h2>Scholarships 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Melbourne International Undergraduate Scholarship (MIUS)</strong> \u2013 50% tuition fee waiver, merit-based, 100+ awards annually</li><li><strong>Melbourne International Research Scholarship (MIRS)</strong> \u2013 Full tuition + stipend AUD $28,092 annually, for research postgraduate</li><li><strong>India-Specific Excellence Scholarships</strong> \u2013 \u20b98-12 LPA for exceptional Indian students, 50+ awards</li><li><strong>Vice-Chancellor's International Scholarship</strong> \u2013 Up to 100% fees + living allowance, highly competitive, 10 awards globally</li><li><strong>Destination Australia Scholarship</strong> \u2013 AUD $15,000 annually for regional study, Australian government-funded</li></ul><h2>Admission Requirements</h2><p><strong>Undergraduate:</strong> HSC/Class 12 (60%+ or equivalent), IELTS 6.5 (6.0 each band) or TOEFL iBT 79. <strong>Postgraduate:</strong> Bachelor's degree (65%+ GPA or equivalent), IELTS 6.5-7.0 depending on program. Documents: passport, transcripts, statement of purpose, CV, LOR (2 for postgraduate). GMAT/GRE required for MBA and some research programs (GMAT 650+).</p><h2>Application Deadlines 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>Semester 1 (February 2025):</strong> Applications closed (Early applications 2024). <strong>Semester 2 (July 2025):</strong> Apply by April 30, 2025. <strong>Semester 1 2026 (February):</strong> Apply by September 30, 2025. Rolling admissions mean earlier applications increase chances significantly.</p><h2>Campus Life</h2><p>On-campus housing costs \u20b98-12 LPA. University provides 4,000+ student accommodation beds. World-class facilities include 15 libraries, sports complex with Olympic-standard facilities, student theater, 200+ student clubs. Melbourne is consistently ranked world's most livable city with vibrant cultural scene, excellent public transport, and strong Indian community support networks.</p><h2>Career Outcomes</h2><p><strong>Graduate Employment Rate: 94.4%</strong> within 6 months of graduation. Average salary: AUD $65,000-75,000 annually. Top employers: Deloitte, Goldman Sachs, Google Australia, EY, PWC, Commonwealth Bank, Microsoft. Strong alumni network across global tec",
