    slug: "chinese-government-scholarship-csc-2025-26-guide",
    excerpt: "CSC Chinese Government Scholarship 2025-26: eligibility, benefits, deadlines & how to apply. Complete guide for Indian students with fees in INR.",
    content: "<h2>Scholarship Overview</h2><p>The <strong>Chinese Government Scholarship (CSC)</strong> is offered by the Ministry of Education of the People's Republic of China and administered through the China Scholarship Council. This prestigious scholarship aims to support outstanding international students in pursuing academic excellence in China. For the 2025-26 academic year, approximately <strong>12,000+ international students</strong> will be selected, with Indian students comprising roughly <strong>800-1,000 positions</strong>. The scholarship covers studies at top-tier Chinese universities including Tsinghua University, Peking University, and Fudan University.</p><h2>What It Covers: Complete Benefits Breakdown</h2><p>The CSC scholarship provides comprehensive coverage across multiple categories:</p><ul><li><strong>Tuition Fees:</strong> 100% covered (\u20b94-6 lakhs annually depending on program type, fully waived)</li><li><strong>Monthly Stipend:</strong> \u00a51,500-3,500 (~\u20b915,000-35,000 per month) depending on study level and program category</li><li><strong>Accommodation:</strong> Free university dormitory or monthly housing allowance of \u00a5300-700 (~\u20b93,000-7,000)</li><li><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Annual comprehensive medical coverage included</li><li><strong>Flight Allowance:</strong> One-way international airfare reimbursement (~\u20b930,000-50,000 for Indian students)</li><li><strong>Research/Living Allowance:</strong> Additional funds for doctoral students and researchers</li></ul><p><strong>Total Annual Value:</strong> Approximately <strong>\u20b92.5-4 lakhs</strong> saved per student. Masters students receive higher stipends than bachelor's level applicants.</p><h2>Eligibility Requirements</h2><p>Meet these essential criteria to qualify:</p><ul><li><strong>Nationality:</strong> Non-Chinese citizens (Indian students eligible)</li><li><strong>Age:</strong> Generally under 35 years (Bachelor's: under 25; Masters: under 30; PhD: under 35)</li><li><strong>Academic Level:</strong> Bachelor's, Master's, or PhD programs accepted</li><li><strong>Academic Performance:</strong> Minimum GPA 3.0/4.0 or 80% in last qualification</li><li><strong>Language:</strong> Proficiency in English or Chinese (HSK Level 4+ for Chinese-taught programs)</li><li><strong>Health:</strong> Valid health certificate required at enrollment</li><li><strong>No Criminal Record:</strong> Clean background essential</li></ul><h2>2025-2026 Application Timeline</h2><table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse;\"><tr style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\"><strong>Event</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\"><strong>Date</strong></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">Application Portal Opens</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">January 15, 2025</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">Application Deadline</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">March 31, 2025</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">Preliminary Results</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">June 2025</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">Final Announcement</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">August 15, 2025</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">Program Start</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ccc; padding:10px;\">September 2025</td></tr></table><h2>Required Documents Checklist</h2><ul><li>Completed online application form (CSC platform)</li><li>Passport copy (bio-data page)</li><li>Undergraduate/Master's degree certificate + transcripts</li><li>Proof of English/Chinese proficiency (TOEFL, IELTS, or HSK)</li><li>Statement of Purpose (500 words)</li><li>2-3 Academic recommendation letters from professors</li><li>Medical examination report (Form JW202)</li><li>Research proposal (for Master's/PhD applicants)</li><li>Proof of financial capability (bank statement ~\u20b95 lakhs)</li></ul><h2>How to Apply: Step-by-Step Process</h2><ol><li><strong>Visit Official Portal:</strong> Go to <strong>www.csc.edu.cn</strong> (English version available)</li><li><strong>Create Account:</strong> Register with email and set secure password</li><li><strong>Complete Profile:</strong> Fill personal, educational, and contact information accurately</li><li><strong>Upload Documents:</strong> Scan and upload all required documents (PDF/JPG format, max 5MB each)</li><li><strong>Select University & Program:</strong> Choose from 300+ partner institutions and desired degree level</li><li><strong>Specify Study Area:</strong> Select discipline (Engineering, Medicine, Business, etc.)</li><li><strong>Submit Application:</strong> Review all entries carefully before final submission</li><li><strong>Track Status:</strong> Monitor application progress via portal dashboard</li><li><strong>Interview Notification:</strong> Selected candidates receive interview call (May-June 2025)</li></ol><h2>Selection ",
