    content: "<h2>University of Toronto Overview</h2><p>The University of Toronto, founded in 1827, ranks <strong>10th globally in the QS World University Rankings 2025</strong> and is Canada's #1 university. Located in Toronto, Ontario, with three campuses (St. George, Scarborough, Mississauga), U of T enrolls 98,000+ students across all levels. International students comprise approximately <strong>34% of the student body</strong>, with over 12,000 Indian students currently enrolled\u2014the largest international cohort.</p><h2>Why Choose University of Toronto?</h2><ul><li><strong>Research Excellence:</strong> U of T ranks in the top 10 for research output globally with annual R&D spending exceeding CAD 430 million</li><li><strong>Notable Alumni:</strong> 3 Fields Medal winners, 9 Nobel Prize laureates, including Malala Yousafzai</li><li><strong>Industry Connections:</strong> Strong partnerships with Google, Microsoft, Shopify, and leading Canadian tech companies</li><li><strong>Academic Reputation:</strong> Consistently ranked #1 in Canada across all major ranking systems</li></ul><h2>Popular Courses 2025-2026</h2><table><tr><th>Program</th><th>Duration</th><th>Career Outcomes</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Engineering (BASc)</strong></td><td>4 years</td><td>99.1% employment within 6 months; avg. salary CAD 78,000/year</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Medicine (MD)</strong></td><td>4 years</td><td>100% licensure rate; avg. salary CAD 250,000+/year</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Computer Science (BSc)</strong></td><td>4 years</td><td>98% employed; avg. starting salary CAD 85,000/year</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Business Administration (Rotman MBA)</strong></td><td>2 years</td><td>95% employed within 3 months; avg. salary CAD 115,000/year</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Law (JD)</strong></td><td>3 years</td><td>97% bar passage rate; avg. salary CAD 120,000+/year</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Data Science (MSc)</strong></td><td>2 years</td><td>96% employment rate; avg. salary CAD 95,000/year</td></tr></table><h2>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>Undergraduate Programs (International Students):</strong></p><ul><li>Engineering: CAD 66,500/year (~\u20b935.5 lakhs/year)</li><li>Medicine: CAD 85,000/year (~\u20b945.5 lakhs/year)</li><li>Commerce/Business: CAD 52,000/year (~\u20b927.8 lakhs/year)</li><li>Arts & Science: CAD 35,000/year (~\u20b918.7 lakhs/year)</li></ul><p><strong>Postgraduate Programs (International Students):</strong></p><ul><li>MBA (Rotman): CAD 110,000/year (~\u20b958.9 lakhs/year)</li><li>Master's Programs: CAD 35,000-75,000/year (~\u20b918.7-40.2 lakhs/year)</li></ul><p><strong>Living Costs (Monthly):</strong> CAD 1,500-2,200 (~\u20b980,000-1,17,000) including accommodation, food, and transport.</p><p><strong>Total Annual Cost:</strong> Approximately CAD 52,000-95,000 (~\u20b927.8-50.9 lakhs) for international undergraduate students.</p><h2>Scholarships & Financial Aid</h2><ul><li><strong>Lester B. Pearson International Scholarship:</strong> Full tuition + living expenses; open to top international applicants; ~CAD 75,000/year (~\u20b940.2 lakhs)</li><li><strong>International Entrance Scholarship:</strong> CAD 10,000-25,000 (~\u20b95.4-13.4 lakhs); based on academic merit</li><li><strong>University of Toronto Merit Scholarship:</strong> CAD 5,000-50,000 (~\u20b92.7-26.8 lakhs); renewable annually</li><li><strong>President's Entrance Scholarship:</strong> CAD 10,000-50,000 (~\u20b95.4-26.8 lakhs); for exceptional students</li><li><strong>Faculty-Specific Awards:</strong> Engineering Excellence Scholarship up to CAD 30,000 (~\u20b916 lakhs)</li></ul><p><strong>Loan Options for Indian Students:</strong> Axis Bank, ICICI Bank, and SBI offer education loans up to \u20b92 crore at 8-10% interest for Canadian universities.</p><h2>Admission Requirements</h2><ul><li><strong>Minimum GPA:</strong> 3.5-3.8/4.0 (varies by program)</li><li><strong>IELTS:</strong> 6.5 minimum (7.0+ preferred); TOEFL: 100 iBT</li><li><strong>Required Documents:</strong> School transcripts, standardized test scores (SAT/ACT for US applicants), 2 reference letters, personal statement</li><li><strong>Program-Specific:</strong> Engineering/Medicine require additional assessments; MBA requires GMAT (600+) or GRE (320+)</li></ul><h2>Application Deadlines 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Fall 2025 (September):</strong> Undergraduate deadline: January 15, 2025; Graduate: January 15-April 30, 2025 (program-dependent)</li><li><strong>Spring 2026 (January):</strong> Limited programs available; deadline: September 1, 2025</li></ul><h2>Campus Life & Accommodation</h2><p><strong>On-Campus Housing Cost:</strong> CAD 800-1,400/month (~\u20b942,800-74,900) for residence halls. U of T guarantees first-year housing. Campus offers 300+ clubs, modern athletic facilities, libraries with 10 million books, and research labs.</p><h2>Career Outcomes & Placement</h2><ul><li><strong>Graduate Employment Rate:</strong> 94.5% employed within 6 months of graduation</li><li><strong>Top Employers:</strong> Google, Microsoft, Goldman Sachs, Canadian Medical Association, BMO Financial ",
