    excerpt: "Complete Canada student visa guide 2025-2026: eligibility, fees (\u20b922,500), documents & step-by-step application. Apply now with EduDhruv.",
    content: "<h2>Understanding Canada Student Visa: Your Complete 2025-2026 Guide</h2>\n\n<h3>What is a Canada Student Visa?</h3>\n<p>A Canada student visa, officially called a \"Study Permit,\" is a document allowing international students to legally study at Designated Learning Institutions (DLIs) in Canada. Over <strong>800,000 international students</strong> currently study in Canada, with Indian students comprising the largest cohort at <strong>over 380,000 (2024 data)</strong>. If you're planning to pursue higher education in Canada for more than 6 months, you'll need this permit.</p>\n\n<h3>2025-2026 Key Updates & Changes</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Biometric Requirements:</strong> All applicants must provide biometrics (fingerprints and photos) at application or port of entry</li>\n<li><strong>Financial Proof Increased:</strong> Proof of funds now requires documentation for entire program duration plus living expenses</li>\n<li><strong>English Language Standards:</strong> IELTS/TOEFL scores must be from tests taken within 2 years</li>\n<li><strong>Processing Priority:</strong> Express processing available for select countries including India (15 days for selected applicants)</li>\n<li><strong>Work Permit Policy:</strong> Post-graduation work permit duration remains tied to study program length (maximum 3 years)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Eligibility Requirements</h3>\n<p>You must meet these core requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Have an acceptance letter from a Designated Learning Institution (DLI)</li>\n<li>Prove financial support (\u20b918-25 lakhs minimum, depending on program length)</li>\n<li>Show ties to your home country (family, property, employment)</li>\n<li>Pass a medical examination (if required)</li>\n<li>Not have a criminal record</li>\n<li>Demonstrate English/French proficiency (IELTS 6.0+ or equivalent)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Required Documents Checklist</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Valid passport (minimum 2 years validity)</li>\n<li>Acceptance letter from DLI (original/official digital copy)</li>\n<li>Proof of financial support (bank statements, sponsor letters)</li>\n<li>Identity documents (birth certificate, Aadhaar)</li>\n<li>Medical examination results (if requested)</li>\n<li>Police clearance certificate</li>\n<li>English language test scores (IELTS/TOEFL)</li>\n<li>Curriculum vitae and statement of purpose</li>\n<li>Academic transcripts and diplomas</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Financial Requirements 2025-2026</h3>\n<table>\n<tr><th>Item</th><th>Amount (CAD)</th><th>Amount (INR)</th></tr>\n<tr><td>Tuition (1 year, average)</td><td>CAD 15,000-25,000</td><td>\u20b99,00,000-15,00,000</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Living expenses (annual)</td><td>CAD 15,000-20,000</td><td>\u20b99,00,000-12,00,000</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Total for 4-year program</td><td>CAD 120,000-180,000</td><td>\u20b972,00,000-1,08,00,000</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Study Permit Fee</td><td>CAD 150</td><td>\u20b99,000</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Biometric Collection</td><td>CAD 85</td><td>\u20b95,100</td></tr>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Financing Options for Indian Students:</strong> Leading Indian banks like SBI, HDFC, and ICICI offer education loans up to \u20b940 lakhs with 6-month MORATORIUM periods. Apply 3-4 months before program start.</p>\n\n<h3>Step-by-Step Application Process</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Get DLI Acceptance Letter:</strong> Apply to Canadian institution and receive official acceptance</li>\n<li><strong>Create Visitor/Study Permit Account:</strong> Visit <strong>canada.ca/study</strong> and log into your account</li>\n<li><strong>Gather Documents:</strong> Organize all required documents (see checklist above)</li>\n<li><strong>Book Biometrics Appointment:</strong> Register at nearest VAC India center (<strong>canadavac.com</strong>) for fingerprints</li>\n<li><strong>Submit Online Application:</strong> Complete the form with personal and financial details on portal</li>\n<li><strong>Pay Application Fee:</strong> Fees are CAD 235 total (Study Permit + Biometric)</li>\n<li><strong>Receive Decision:</strong> Most Indian applicants get responses within 15-30 days for standard processing</li>\n<li><strong>Arrange Travel:</strong> Once approved, book your flights and accommodation</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h3>Visa Fees 2025-2026</h3>\n<p>Study Permit Application: <strong>CAD 150 (\u20b99,000)</strong></p>\n<p>Biometric Collection Fee: <strong>CAD 85 (\u20b95,100)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Total: CAD 235 (\u20b914,100)</strong></p>\n<p>Note: Fees are non-refundable. Payment processed via credit card on the online portal.</p>\n\n<h3>Processing Time 2025-2026</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Standard Processing:</strong> 4-12 weeks (most common)</li>\n<li><strong>Express Processing (India):</strong> 2-4 weeks (available for select profiles)</li>\n<li><strong>During Peak Season (May-August):</strong> Can extend to 16+ weeks</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Apply 4-6 months before your program start date. Indian students submitting in January-February for fall intake have highest success rates.</p>\n\n<h3>Top 5 Common Rejection Reasons</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Insufficient Financial Proof:</strong> Bank statements don't match funds nee",
