    slug: "nus-singapore-complete-guide-2025",
    excerpt: "NUS Singapore fees, courses, admission requirements for international students 2025. Scholarships, living costs in INR, application deadlines & career outcomes.",
    content: "<h2>National University of Singapore (NUS) \u2014 Complete Guide 2025</h2>\n\n<h3>University Overview</h3>\n<p>The National University of Singapore (NUS) is Asia's top-ranked university and consistently ranks <strong>8th globally in QS World Rankings 2025</strong>. Founded in 1905, NUS has evolved into a world-class institution with a sprawling 156-hectare campus in Kent Ridge. The university enrolls over 37,000 students, with <strong>33% international students</strong> from 100+ countries, including a thriving Indian student community of approximately 2,200 students.</p>\n\n<h3>Why Choose NUS?</h3>\n<p>NUS excels in research, innovation, and industry partnerships. The university produces graduates who lead Fortune 500 companies globally. Notable alumni include leaders in tech, finance, and public policy. Research strengths span engineering, life sciences, business, and computing \u2014 with NUS ranking <strong>1st in Asia for research output</strong>. The university's strong connections with Singapore's thriving economy create exceptional internship and job opportunities.</p>\n\n<h3>Popular Courses 2025-2026</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Computer Science (B.Comp)</strong> \u2014 4 years; graduates earn average SGD 5,000/month (\u20b93,00,000 annually); top employers: Google, Meta, Microsoft</li>\n<li><strong>Electrical Engineering (BEng)</strong> \u2014 4 years; placement rate 98%; average starting salary SGD 4,500/month (\u20b92,70,000)</li>\n<li><strong>MBA (Full-Time)</strong> \u2014 12-16 months; graduates earn average USD 150,000+ annually (\u20b91,25,00,000+); ranked top 10 in Asia</li>\n<li><strong>Business Analytics (MSc)</strong> \u2014 12 months; 95% employment within 6 months; average salary SGD 5,500/month (\u20b93,30,000)</li>\n<li><strong>Medicine (MBBS)</strong> \u2014 5 years; highly competitive; graduates work across Asia's leading hospitals</li>\n<li><strong>Law (LLB)</strong> \u2014 4 years; 92% bar passage rate; average starting salary SGD 5,000/month (\u20b93,00,000)</li>\n<li><strong>Civil Engineering (BEng)</strong> \u2014 4 years; placement 97%; average salary SGD 4,200/month (\u20b92,50,000)</li>\n<li><strong>Master of Science in Finance</strong> \u2014 12 months; graduates work at investment banks and hedge funds globally</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h3>\n<p><strong>Undergraduate Programs (Annual):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Engineering, Science, Business: USD 23,000-26,000 (\u20b919,00,000-21,50,000)</li>\n<li>Medicine, Law: USD 27,000-29,000 (\u20b922,30,000-24,00,000)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Postgraduate Programs (Annual):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>MBA: USD 84,000-90,000 (\u20b969,50,000-74,50,000) for full 12-16 months</li>\n<li>MSc Programs: USD 25,000-35,000 (\u20b920,70,000-28,90,000)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Living Costs (Monthly):</strong> USD 1,200-1,500 (\u20b999,000-1,24,000) including accommodation, food, and transport. <strong>On-campus hostel: USD 400-600/month (\u20b933,000-50,000).</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Total Annual Cost:</strong> UG: USD 38,000-45,000 (\u20b931,50,000-37,30,000); PG: USD 45,000-125,000 (\u20b937,30,000-1,03,50,000)</p>\n\n<h3>Scholarships & Financial Aid 2025-2026</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>NUS Merit Scholarship</strong> \u2014 Up to 100% tuition + SGD 1,000/month stipend (\u20b960,000); for top academic achievers</li>\n<li><strong>ASEAN Scholarship</strong> \u2014 Full tuition + SGD 800/month (\u20b948,000); for ASEAN nationals including Indian expat students</li>\n<li><strong>NUS Research Scholarship</strong> \u2014 Covers fees + SGD 2,000/month (\u20b91,20,000); for PhD candidates</li>\n<li><strong>President's Graduate Fellowship</strong> \u2014 Full coverage + monthly allowance; highly selective for Master's</li>\n<li><strong>India-NUS Education Loan</strong> \u2014 Partner banks (ICICI, Axis, HDFC) offer educational loans up to \u20b950 lakhs at 7-8.5% interest for Indian students</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Admission Requirements</h3>\n<p><strong>Undergraduate:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>High school GPA: 3.5/4.0 minimum or equivalent</li>\n<li>IELTS: 6.5+ (minimum) or TOEFL iBT: 87+</li>\n<li>SAT: 1450+ or ACE 31+ or equivalent</li>\n<li>Transcripts, 2 recommendation letters, personal statement</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Postgraduate:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor's degree with GPA 3.2+</li>\n<li>IELTS: 6.5+ or TOEFL iBT: 85+</li>\n<li>GMAT/GRE (MBA requires 700+; MSc programs vary)</li>\n<li>Work experience: MBA typically requires 3+ years</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Application Deadlines 2025-2026</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Undergraduate Fall 2025:</strong> January 10, 2025 (Early); February 28, 2025 (Regular)</li>\n<li><strong>Undergraduate Spring 2026:</strong> October 1, 2025</li>\n<li><strong>MBA Fall 2025:</strong> December 15, 2024 (Round 1); January 31, 2025 (Round 2)</li>\n<li><strong>Master's Programs:</strong> Vary by program; typically December 2024 - April 2025</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Campus Life & Housing</h3>\n<p>NUS offers vibrant residential college life with <strong>on-campus housing for 30% of students</strong>. Hostels cost SGD 400-600/month (\u20b924,000-36,000). The campus features 6 libraries, 30+ student clubs, 2 gymnasia, Olympic-size swimming pool, and sports facilities. Fo",
