    content: "<h2>What is a Canada Student Visa?</h2><p>A Canada student visa (also called a study permit) is an official document that allows international students to study full-time at designated learning institutions in Canada. Think of it as your legal entry ticket\u2014without it, you cannot study in Canada as an international student. For Indian students specifically, this is one of the most sought-after study permits globally, with over 890,000 international students enrolled as of 2024.</p><p><strong>Who needs it?</strong> Any student from outside Canada planning to study for more than 6 months at a Canadian institution requires a study permit.</p><h2>Key Updates for 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Temporary Resident Visa (TRV) requirement change:</strong> As of November 2024, some countries including India no longer require a separate TRV alongside the study permit application\u2014streamlining the process.</li><li><strong>Biometric requirements:</strong> All applicants must provide biometrics (fingerprints and photo). Locations are available across India.</li><li><strong>New intake caps:</strong> Canada will maintain stricter international student intake limits\u2014meaning earlier applications get priority.</li><li><strong>AI-powered document verification:</strong> IRCC now uses advanced technology to verify document authenticity, so submit genuine documents only.</li></ul><h2>Eligibility Requirements</h2><p>You must meet ALL of these criteria:</p><ul><li>Be accepted to a <strong>Designated Learning Institution (DLI)</strong> in Canada</li><li>Prove you have <strong>sufficient financial support</strong> for tuition and living expenses</li><li>Have a valid passport (minimum 2 years validity recommended)</li><li>Pass a medical exam (if required)</li><li>Pass security and background checks</li><li>Demonstrate ties to your home country (intent to return)</li><li>Be in good health and not pose security risks</li></ul><h2>Required Documents Checklist</h2><ul><li>\u2713 Valid passport (copy of bio page)</li><li>\u2713 Letter of Acceptance from DLI</li><li>\u2713 Proof of financial support (see amounts below)</li><li>\u2713 Birth certificate or equivalent ID</li><li>\u2713 Police certificate/PCC from last 10 years of residence</li><li>\u2713 Medical exam report (if applicable)</li><li>\u2713 Proof of English/French proficiency (IELTS, TOEFL, etc.)</li><li>\u2713 Educational transcripts from previous institutions</li><li>\u2713 Statement of Purpose (SOP) letter</li><li>\u2713 Proof of relationship to sponsor (if applicable)</li></ul><h2>Financial Requirements 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>You must prove you can cover:</strong></p><table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:15px 0;\"><tr style=\"background:#f5f5f5;\"><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>Expense</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>CAD</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>INR (approx.)</strong></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Tuition (per year, avg.)</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">CAD 15,000-25,000</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">\u20b97.5-12.5 lakhs</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Living expenses (per year)</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">CAD 20,000-30,000</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">\u20b910-15 lakhs</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>Minimum total (1 year)</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>CAD 35,000</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>\u20b917.5 lakhs</strong></td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>4-year program minimum</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>CAD 140,000</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>\u20b970 lakhs</strong></td></tr></table><p><strong>For Indian students:</strong> Popular education loan options include SBI Student Loan Scheme (up to \u20b940 lakhs) and HDFC Bank Education Loan (up to \u20b91 crore), both with competitive interest rates starting at 8-9% p.a.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Application Process</h2><ol><li><strong>Get acceptance letter:</strong> Apply and receive admission from a DLI at <a href=\"https://www.cicic.ca/\" target=\"_blank\">www.cicic.ca</a></li><li><strong>Gather documents:</strong> Compile everything from the checklist above</li><li><strong>Create IRCC account:</strong> Register at <a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/ircc\" target=\"_blank\">www.canada.ca/ircc</a></li><li><strong>Submit online application:</strong> Use the official Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC) portal; paper applications not accepted</li><li><strong>Pay fees:</strong> CAD 150 (\u20b97,500 approx.) via credit/debit card</li><li><strong>Provide biometrics:</strong> Visit a biometric collection center in India within specified timeframe</li><li><strong>Attend medical exam:</strong> If requested, visit ",
