    excerpt: "Cambridge University admission fees courses 2025 guide. Learn tuition, scholarships, requirements & deadlines for international & Indian students.",
    content: "<h2>University of Cambridge Overview</h2><p>The University of Cambridge, founded in 1209, stands as one of the world's most prestigious institutions. Located in Cambridge, England, it ranks <strong>#2 globally in QS Rankings 2025</strong> and maintains a world-class reputation across all academic disciplines. With a student population of approximately 20,000 and <strong>37% international students</strong>, Cambridge offers a truly global academic community while preserving its historic college-based system unique to British education.</p><h2>Why Choose Cambridge University?</h2><p>Cambridge excels in research excellence with <strong>over \u00a3700 million in annual research funding</strong>. The university boasts an exceptional alumni network including 120+ Nobel Prize winners, Stephen Hawking, Charles Darwin, and Cheryl Cole. Notable Indian alumni include CV Raman (Nobel Laureate), Jawaharlal Nehru, and Indra Nooyi (Former PepsiCo CEO). Cambridge's tutorial system provides unmatched personal attention\u2014small group teaching with world-leading scholars is standard. The college system creates tight-knit communities within the university's larger structure, fostering intellectual growth and lifelong networks.</p><h2>Popular Courses & Programs 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Computer Science (MPhil/BA)</strong> \u2013 2-3 years; Career outcome: Software engineer, AI researcher (avg. \u00a360,000+ starting salary)</li><li><strong>Medicine (6 years)</strong> \u2013 Highly competitive; Graduates work at top hospitals globally; avg. \u00a350,000 starting</li><li><strong>Engineering (BA/MEng)</strong> \u2013 3-4 years; Top employers: Tesla, Google, Airbus; avg. salary \u00a355,000+</li><li><strong>Law (BA)</strong> \u2013 3 years; Direct path to legal practice; avg. \u00a370,000+ for corporate law roles</li><li><strong>Natural Sciences (BA)</strong> \u2013 3-4 years; Research-focused; avg. \u00a345,000+ starting salary</li><li><strong>Economics (BA)</strong> \u2013 3 years; Top employers: IMF, World Bank, Goldman Sachs; avg. \u00a375,000+</li><li><strong>Classics (BA)</strong> \u2013 3 years; Strong humanities foundation; avg. \u00a340,000+ starting</li><li><strong>Philosophy (BA)</strong> \u2013 3 years; Develops critical thinking; avg. \u00a342,000+ starting</li></ul><h2>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h2><table><tr><th>Category</th><th>Annual Fee (USD)</th><th>Annual Fee (INR)</th></tr><tr><td>Undergraduate (International)</td><td>$27,000-$32,000</td><td>\u20b922.5-26.6 Lakhs</td></tr><tr><td>Postgraduate (International)</td><td>$24,000-$45,000</td><td>\u20b920-37.5 Lakhs</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly Living Costs</td><td>$1,200-$1,500</td><td>\u20b91-1.25 Lakhs</td></tr><tr><td>Total Annual Cost (UG)</td><td>$42,600-$50,000</td><td>\u20b935.5-41.5 Lakhs</td></tr></table><p><strong>Note:</strong> Fees vary by college and subject. Medicine and Natural Sciences are at the higher end. Indian students currently number around 1,100+ across all levels.</p><h2>Scholarships & Financial Aid 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Cambridge International Scholarships</strong> \u2013 Full tuition + stipend (up to \u00a315,000/year); Merit-based; highly competitive</li><li><strong>Ramanujan Scholarship for Indian Students</strong> \u2013 Covers 50% tuition (\u20b911-18 Lakhs/year); Requires STEM background; 20+ awards annually</li><li><strong>Chevening Scholarships</strong> \u2013 Full tuition + living allowance (\u20b920 Lakhs+); UK government-funded; preference for Indian professionals</li><li><strong>Cambridge Trusts</strong> \u2013 Various amounts (\u20b95-15 Lakhs); Subject and nationality-specific; 50+ awards available</li><li><strong>College-Based Awards</strong> \u2013 Variable amounts; College-dependent; Check your assigned college website</li></ul><h2>Admission Requirements 2025</h2><ul><li><strong>Academic Qualifications:</strong> IB: 40+/45; A-Levels: A*A*A minimum; CBSE: 95%+ with strong performance in entrance exams</li><li><strong>English Language:</strong> IELTS: 7.5+ (minimum 7.0 in each component) OR TOEFL: 100+ (iBT)</li><li><strong>Subject-Specific Tests:</strong> Engineering: STEP or TMUA; Medicine: UCAT (Undergraduate); some subjects require written assessments</li><li><strong>Documents Required:</strong> Passport, school transcripts, teacher references (2-3), personal statement, standardized test scores</li><li><strong>Indian Students:</strong> JEE/NEET scores considered; interview component is mandatory for most subjects</li></ul><h2>Application Deadlines 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Fall 2025 Entry:</strong> UCAS deadline: October 15, 2024 (for 2025 entry)</li><li><strong>Fall 2026 Entry:</strong> UCAS deadline: October 15, 2025</li><li><strong>Interviews:</strong> November-December for Fall entry</li><li><strong>Decisions Released:</strong> January 15 annually</li><li><strong>Note:</strong> Some postgraduate programs have rolling admissions; Apply early (November onwards)</li></ul><h2>Campus Life & Accommodation</h2><p>Cambridge guarantees accommodation for undergraduate students in college rooms. <strong>Annual housing cost: \u00a33,000-\u00a36,000 (\u20b92.5-5 Lakhs)</strong>, signif",
