    id: "1886",
    title: "IELTS vs TOEFL for Indian Students 2025: Complete Comparison",
    slug: "ielts-vs-toefl-indian-students-2025-2",
    excerpt: "IELTS vs TOEFL Indian students 2025 comparison. Fees, universities, scholarships & visa guide. Make the right choice today!",
    content: "<h2>IELTS vs TOEFL for Indian Students 2025: Which Should You Choose?</h2>\n\n<p>If you're an Indian student planning to study abroad in 2025-2026, you've probably asked yourself: <strong>IELTS vs TOEFL Indian students 2025\u2014which is better for me?</strong> Both tests are globally recognized, but they differ in format, cost, and acceptance. Let me break this down so you can decide confidently.</p>\n\n<h3>Why Choose IELTS for Indian Students?</h3>\n\n<p>IELTS (International English Language Testing System) is the preferred choice for <strong>over 1.4 million Indian students in 2025</strong>. It's accepted across UK, Australia, Canada, and increasingly in USA universities. The test feels more conversational\u2014you sit with a real examiner for speaking, which many Indian students find less intimidating than TOEFL's computer-based format. Plus, IELTS fees are \u20b914,600 (approximately USD 175), making it affordable for budget-conscious families.</p>\n\n<h3>Why Choose TOEFL for Indian Students?</h3>\n\n<p>TOEFL (Test of English as a Foreign Language) dominates in US universities\u2014all 150+ top American institutions require it. With <strong>around 850,000 Indian test-takers annually in 2025</strong>, it's increasingly popular among students targeting Ivy League schools. TOEFL costs \u20b920,950 (USD 250), and the computer-based format means your English listening and reading skills get authentic practice with real academic content.</p>\n\n<h3>Top 3 Universities Accepting Both Tests (QS Rankings 2025)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>University of Oxford (UK) \u2014 Rank #3 QS 2025:</strong> IELTS 7.0+ or TOEFL 110+</li>\n<li><strong>MIT (USA) \u2014 Rank #2 QS 2025:</strong> TOEFL preferred, minimum 100 (IELTS 7.5+ accepted)</li>\n<li><strong>University of Melbourne (Australia) \u2014 Rank #37 QS 2025:</strong> IELTS 6.5+ or TOEFL 79+</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Fees Comparison in Indian Rupees (2025)</h3>\n\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 20px 0;\">\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f0f0f0;\">\n<th style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px; text-align: left;\">Test Name</th>\n<th style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px; text-align: left;\">Exam Fee (INR)</th>\n<th style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px; text-align: left;\">Test Date Availability</th>\n<th style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px; text-align: left;\">Results Timeline</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\"><strong>IELTS Academic</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">\u20b914,600</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">48+ times/year in India</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">13 calendar days</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f9f9f9;\">\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\"><strong>TOEFL iBT</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">\u20b920,950</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">50+ times/year in India</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">6 days (score online)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\"><strong>IELTS Retake</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">\u20b914,600</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">Available immediately</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">13 calendar days</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f9f9f9;\">\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\"><strong>TOEFL Retake</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">\u20b920,950</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">12 days wait minimum</td>\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px;\">6 days</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Best Loan Option for Indian Students</h3>\n\n<p><strong>State Bank of India (SBI) Student Loan Scheme 2025:</strong> Covers test prep coaching, exam fees, and university admission fees up to <strong>\u20b91,00,000 at 7.85% annual interest</strong> (for amounts above \u20b950,000). You can apply 3 months before your test date. Processing time: 15-20 days. No collateral required for loans up to \u20b950,000. Contact your nearest SBI branch for the Education Loan Desk.</p>\n\n<h3>Visa: 3 Key Documents Needed (Both Tests)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Original test score report</strong> \u2014 IELTS TRF (Test Report Form) or TOEFL score PDF</li>\n<li><strong>University acceptance letter</strong> \u2014 Conditional or unconditional offer</li>\n<li><strong>Proof of financial support</strong> \u2014 Bank statements, scholarship letter, or sponsor affidavit (\u20b925-50 lakhs for UK/US/Australia)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Scholarship Worth \u20b918,00,000 Annually</h3>\n\n<p><strong>Chevening Scholarship (UK, 2025-2026):</strong> Covers tuition fees (up to \u00a315,000/year = \u20b915,30,000) + monthly stipend of \u00a31,000 (\u20b91,02,000) for Indian students. Requires IELTS 6.5+ (TOEFL alternative: 92+). Application deadline: October 2025. Over 200 Indian students awarded annually.</p>\n\n<h3>Quick Comparison: IELTS vs TOEFL at a Glance</h3>\n\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 1",
