    slug: "canada-student-visa-requirements-how-to-apply-2025",
    excerpt: "Complete Canada student visa guide 2025-2026: eligibility, documents, fees (\u20b920,715), processing time & application steps for Indian students.",
    content: "<h2>What is a Canada Student Visa?</h2><p>A Canada Student Visa (also called a study permit) is an official document that allows international students to study at designated learning institutions in Canada. If you're an Indian student planning to pursue education in Canada, you'll need this permit before arrival. It's not just an entry visa\u2014it's your authorization to live and study in Canada for the duration of your program.</p><h2>Who Needs a Canada Student Visa?</h2><p>You need a study permit if:</p><ul><li>You're a citizen of a country outside Canada</li><li>You've received an acceptance letter from a Designated Learning Institution (DLI)</li><li>You plan to study for more than 6 months</li><li>You're a citizen of certain countries (most countries require it; some exempt countries exist)</li></ul><h2>2025-2026 Key Updates</h2><p><strong>Major Changes:</strong> Canada has implemented stricter financial documentation requirements starting January 2025. Indian students must now provide notarized bank statements and proof of fund source. The International Student Program (ISP) cap remains at 364,000 study permits. Processing times have increased by 15-20% due to higher application volumes from South Asian countries.</p><h2>Eligibility Requirements</h2><ul><li><strong>Minimum Age:</strong> Usually 16+ (varies by institution)</li><li><strong>Valid Passport:</strong> Valid for entire study period + return</li><li><strong>Acceptance Letter:</strong> From a DLI-approved institution</li><li><strong>Financial Proof:</strong> Demonstrate ability to cover tuition + living expenses</li><li><strong>Medical Exam:</strong> May be required (authorized panel doctor)</li><li><strong>Police Clearance:</strong> Criminal background check if applicable</li><li><strong>Language Proficiency:</strong> English/French (IELTS, TOEFL, CELPIP, TCF accepted)</li></ul><h2>Required Documents Checklist 2025-2026</h2><ul><li>Valid passport (front & back pages)</li><li>Acceptance letter from DLI (original or official copy)</li><li>Notarized bank statements (last 4 months minimum)</li><li>Proof of fund source (affidavit from sponsor)</li><li>Tuition fee payment proof or receipt</li><li>Proof of identity (birth certificate/national ID)</li><li>Curriculum vitae (CV)</li><li>Statement of purpose (SOP)</li><li>Language test results (if required)</li><li>Medical exam report (if requested)</li><li>Police clearance certificate (if applicable)</li><li>Parental consent (if under 18)</li></ul><h2>Financial Requirements for Indian Students 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>Proof of Funds Needed:</strong></p><table><tr><td><strong>Program Duration</strong></td><td><strong>Estimated CAD</strong></td><td><strong>Estimated INR</strong></td></tr><tr><td>1 Year</td><td>CAD $30,000-45,000</td><td>\u20b916,50,000 - \u20b924,75,000</td></tr><tr><td>2 Years</td><td>CAD $50,000-70,000</td><td>\u20b927,50,000 - \u20b938,50,000</td></tr><tr><td>4 Years (Bachelor's)</td><td>CAD $80,000-120,000</td><td>\u20b944,00,000 - \u20b966,00,000</td></tr></table><p><strong>Living Expenses (Annual):</strong> CAD $15,000-20,000 (\u20b98,25,000 - \u20b911,00,000). Canada accepts funds from parents, relatives, or personal savings. Bank loans from HDFC, ICICI, Axis Bank, and SBI are available with interest rates between 8.5%-11% per annum.</p><h2>Canada Student Visa Fees 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Application Fee:</strong> CAD $150 (\u20b98,250)</li><li><strong>Biometric Fee:</strong> CAD $85 (\u20b94,680)</li><li><strong>Biometric Collection (in India):</strong> Free at VAC centers</li><li><strong>Processing Fee (if applicable):</strong> CAD $75 (\u20b94,125)</li><li><strong>Total Approx Cost:</strong> CAD $235-310 (\u20b912,925 - \u20b917,050)</li><li><strong>Note:</strong> Fees are non-refundable, even if application is rejected</li></ul><h2>Step-by-Step Application Process</h2><ol><li><strong>Secure Acceptance Letter:</strong> Apply to DLI, receive acceptance letter</li><li><strong>Gather Documents:</strong> Compile all required documents with notarization</li><li><strong>Create Account:</strong> Register on Canada.ca (https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/study-canada.html)</li><li><strong>Complete Application:</strong> Fill IMM 1294 (Application for Study Permit) online</li><li><strong>Pay Fees:</strong> Pay CAD $150 + $85 through secure portal</li><li><strong>Submit Application:</strong> Upload all documents to online portal</li><li><strong>Book Biometrics:</strong> Schedule at nearest VAC (Visa Application Center) in India</li><li><strong>Attend Biometrics:</strong> Visit VAC for fingerprints and photo (\u20b90 cost)</li><li><strong>Track Application:</strong> Monitor status via online account (usually within 4-8 weeks)</li><li><strong>Receive Decision:</strong> Approval letter or request for additional documents</li><li><strong>Arrange Travel:</strong> Book flight and accommodation once approved</li></ol><h2>Processing Time 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Standard Processing:</strong> 4-8 weeks (from biometrics submissio",
