    slug: "eth-zurich-complete-guide-2025-fees-courses",
    excerpt: "ETH Zurich fees, courses & admission 2025-2026 guide for international students. Complete details on tuition, scholarships & application deadlines.",
    content: "<h2>University Overview</h2><p><strong>ETH Zurich (Swiss Federal Institute of Technology)</strong> ranks <strong>#11 globally</strong> in the QS World University Rankings 2025, making it Europe's leading science and technology university. Founded in 1855, this prestigious institution sits in Zurich, Switzerland's financial hub, with a sprawling 38-hectare campus.</p><p>The university hosts approximately <strong>22,000 students</strong> from 120+ countries. International students comprise <strong>42% of the total student population</strong>, with roughly <strong>800-900 Indian students</strong> currently enrolled across undergraduate and postgraduate programs.</p><h2>Why Choose ETH Zurich</h2><p>ETH Zurich is renowned for exceptional research output, boasting <strong>21 Nobel laureates</strong> affiliated with the institution. The university excels in engineering, mathematics, physics, and computer science, offering cutting-edge labs and industry partnerships.</p><ul><li>World-class faculty with strong industry connections</li><li>Collaborative research culture with global recognition</li><li>Strong alumni network (CEOs of Google, Novartis, ABB)</li><li>High graduate employment rate of 97%</li><li>Bilingual education (German and English programs available)</li></ul><h2>Popular Courses 2025-2026</h2><table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:20px 0;\"><tr style=\"background-color:#f5f5f5;\"><th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px; text-align:left;\"><strong>Program</strong></th><th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px; text-align:left;\"><strong>Duration</strong></th><th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px; text-align:left;\"><strong>Career Outcome</strong></th></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">MSc Computer Science</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">2 years</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Tech roles at Google, Microsoft, IBM</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">MSc Mechanical Engineering</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">2 years</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Automotive, aerospace industry positions</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">MSc Civil Engineering</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">2 years</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Infrastructure, consulting roles</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">BSc Physics</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">3 years</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Research, pharmaceutical industry</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">MSc Mathematics</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">2 years</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Finance, tech companies</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">MSc Electrical Engineering</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">2 years</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Energy, semiconductor firms</td></tr></table><h2>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>ETH Zurich fees for international students:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Undergraduate Annual Tuition:</strong> CHF 1,460 (~\u20b91,24,100 INR / $1,750 USD)</li><li><strong>Postgraduate Annual Tuition:</strong> CHF 730 (~\u20b962,050 INR / $875 USD)</li></ul><p><strong>Living Costs (Monthly):</strong></p><ul><li>Accommodation: CHF 800-1,200 (~\u20b968,000-\u20b91,02,000 INR)</li><li>Food & Groceries: CHF 400-600 (~\u20b934,000-\u20b951,000 INR)</li><li>Transportation: CHF 120 (semester pass included)</li><li>Personal expenses: CHF 300-400 (~\u20b925,500-\u20b934,000 INR)</li></ul><p><strong>Total Annual Cost:</strong> CHF 16,000-20,000 (~\u20b913.6-17 lakhs INR / $19,200-24,000 USD)</p><h2>Scholarships Available</h2><ul><li><strong>ETH Zurich Excellence Scholarship:</strong> Full tuition + CHF 16,000 living allowance annually. For high-achieving international students. Covers ~\u20b915+ lakhs INR/year.</li><li><strong>Swiss Government Excellence Scholarships:</strong> CHF 1,500/month (~\u20b91,27,500 INR/month) for master's students. Highly competitive.</li><li><strong>Inlaks Shivdasani Foundation Scholarship:</strong> For Indian students pursuing master's degrees. Covers tuition + living costs (~\u20b912-15 lakhs annually).</li><li><strong>Indian Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR) Scholarship:</strong> CHF 1,300/month for Indian nationals. Merit-based, competitive selection.</li></ul><h2>Admission Requirements</h2><p><strong>Undergraduate:</strong></p><ul><li>High school diploma with strong marks (minimum 85%)</li><li>English proficiency: IELTS 6.5+ or TOEFL 90+</li><li>Mathematics and science prerequisites</li></ul><p><strong>Postgraduate (Master's):</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in relevant field (GPA 3.5+/4.0 preferred)</li><li>IELTS 6.5 or TOEFL 90+</li><li>GRE/GMAT (recommended for some programs)</li><li>Statement of purpose and academic references</li></ul><h2",
