    excerpt: "Complete Canada student visa guide 2025-2026: eligibility, documents, fees (\u20b968,000), processing time & tips for Indian students. Apply now!",
    content: "<h2>What is a Canada Student Visa?</h2><p>A Canada Student Visa (Study Permit) is an official document that allows international students to study at designated learning institutions (DLIs) in Canada. If you're planning to pursue higher education in Canada, you'll need this permit regardless of your home country. For Indian students, this is your gateway to world-class education\u2014Canada hosts over 800,000 international students annually, with Indian students comprising approximately 35% of this population.</p><h2>2025-2026 Key Updates</h2><ul><li><strong>New Intake Cap:</strong> Canada has implemented stricter international student intake policies to manage housing shortages. Study permit approvals are being scrutinized more carefully regarding financial proof and institutional credibility.</li><li><strong>Enhanced Financial Documentation:</strong> Banks must provide detailed verification letters. Self-sponsored applicants face higher scrutiny on fund sources.</li><li><strong>Processing Prioritization:</strong> Express entry processing launched January 2025 for students from priority countries with GIC (Guaranteed Investment Certificate) accounts.</li><li><strong>Biometric Requirement Expansion:</strong> All new applicants must complete biometrics at approved collection centers, including in India.</li></ul><h2>Eligibility Requirements</h2><ul><li>Acceptance letter from a Canadian Designated Learning Institution (DLI)</li><li>Proof of financial support (minimum CAD $20,000-$30,000 per year depending on province)</li><li>English/French language proficiency (IELTS 6.0+ or equivalent)</li><li>Proof of ties to your home country</li><li>Clean criminal record with police certificate</li><li>Medical fitness (chest X-ray and medical exam if required)</li><li>No previous visa violations</li></ul><h2>Required Documents Checklist</h2><ul><li>Valid passport (6+ months validity)</li><li>Acceptance letter from Canadian DLI (must have DLI number)</li><li>Bank statements (last 4 months)</li><li>Educational credentials with IELTS/TOEFL scores</li><li>PAN card, Aadhaar, voter ID (identity documents)</li><li>Parents' income tax returns (last 2 years)</li><li>Employment letters from parents</li><li>Property documents (proof of ties)</li><li>Medical examination report (IME certified)</li><li>Police clearance certificate</li><li>Statement of purpose</li><li>Curriculum vitae</li></ul><h2>Financial Requirements 2025-2026</h2><p>Canada requires proof of funds covering tuition and living expenses:</p><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:20px 0;\"><tr style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"><th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;text-align:left;\">Expense Type</th><th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;text-align:left;\">Amount (CAD)</th><th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;text-align:left;\">Amount (INR)</th></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\">Tuition (per year)</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\">$15,000-$35,000</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\">\u20b99,90,000-\u20b923,10,000</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\">Living Expenses (per year)</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\">$15,000-$20,000</td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\">\u20b99,90,000-\u20b913,20,000</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\"><strong>Total (2-year program)</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\"><strong>$60,000-$90,000</strong></td><td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd;padding:10px;\"><strong>\u20b939,60,000-\u20b959,40,000</strong></td></tr></table><p><strong>Indian Loan Options:</strong> HDFC Bank (up to \u20b940 lakhs), Axis Bank, and SBI offer education loans at 8-10% interest with 2-year moratorium periods post-graduation.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Application Process</h2><ol><li><strong>Receive DLI Acceptance:</strong> Get unconditional offer letter from your Canadian institution</li><li><strong>Create GC Key Account:</strong> Register at https://www.canada.ca/gckey (required for all applications)</li><li><strong>Gather Documents:</strong> Compile all supporting documents with certified English translations</li><li><strong>Complete IMM 1294:</strong> Fill application for study permit form (available on IRCC portal)</li><li><strong>Pay Application Fee:</strong> \u20b968,000 (CAD $100) non-refundable; \u20b99,100 (CAD $13.25) biometric fee</li><li><strong>Submit Online:</strong> Upload all documents to https://www.canada.ca/ircc (immigration portal)</li><li><strong>Complete Biometrics:</strong> Visit approved VFS Global center in India within 30 days</li><li><strong>Receive Decision:</strong> Most decisions come within 4-8 weeks</li><li><strong>Activate eStudy Permit:</strong> Upon approval, create online account to obtain document</li><li><strong>Arrive in Canada:</strong> Present eStudy Permit or printed approval letter at port of entry</li></ol><h2>Visa Fees 2025-2026</h2><ul><li>Study Permit Application Fee: <strong>\u20b968,000</strong> (C",
