    excerpt: "University of Melbourne fees courses admission 2025 guide for Indian students. Tuition costs, scholarships, deadlines & career outcomes explained.",
    content: "<h2>University Overview</h2><p>The University of Melbourne, founded in 1853, is Australia's second-oldest university and consistently ranks among the world's elite institutions. Located in Melbourne, Victoria, the university serves over 48,000 students across its sprawling 22-hectare Parkville campus, with additional facilities in Southbank and Werribee. According to QS World University Rankings 2025, the University of Melbourne ranks <strong>37th globally</strong> and <strong>1st in Australia</strong>. International students comprise approximately 40% of the student body, with over 1,200 Indian students currently enrolled, making it a welcoming destination for Asian scholars.</p><h2>Why Choose University of Melbourne</h2><p>Melbourne excels in research, particularly in medical sciences, engineering, and environmental studies. The university has produced <strong>5 Nobel Prize winners</strong> and counts among its alumni prominent figures like Melinda Gates, Fred Hollows, and Sir Edmund Herring. The institution received <strong>AUD $380 million in research funding</strong> in 2024, demonstrating its commitment to innovation and excellence. Its location in Australia's cultural capital provides unparalleled networking opportunities and internship access to leading global organizations.</p><h2>Popular Courses 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Master of Science (Data Science)</strong> \u2013 2 years; Career path: Data analyst, ML engineer at Google, Deloitte; Average salary: AUD 120,000/year</li><li><strong>Master of Engineering (Software)</strong> \u2013 2 years; Career path: Software architect, tech leadership roles; Average salary: AUD 130,000/year</li><li><strong>Master of Business Administration (MBA)</strong> \u2013 2 years; Career path: Management consultant, finance executive; Average salary: AUD 150,000/year</li><li><strong>Master of Laws (LLM)</strong> \u2013 1-2 years; Career path: International lawyer, corporate counsel; Average salary: AUD 140,000/year</li><li><strong>Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS)</strong> \u2013 6 years; Career path: Practicing physician; Average salary: AUD 180,000/year</li><li><strong>Master of Public Health</strong> \u2013 2 years; Career path: Health policy officer, epidemiologist; Average salary: AUD 110,000/year</li><li><strong>Master of Environmental Engineering</strong> \u2013 2 years; Career path: Sustainability consultant; Average salary: AUD 115,000/year</li></ul><h2>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>Postgraduate Programs (International Students):</strong></p><ul><li>Engineering, IT, Science: AUD 45,000\u201355,000/year (\u20b925,65,000\u201331,35,000 INR)</li><li>Business, Economics: AUD 48,000\u201358,000/year (\u20b927,36,000\u201333,06,000 INR)</li><li>Law, Medicine: AUD 55,000\u201375,000/year (\u20b931,35,000\u201342,75,000 INR)</li></ul><p><strong>Undergraduate Programs (International Students):</strong></p><ul><li>Science, Engineering: AUD 38,000\u201348,000/year (\u20b921,66,000\u201327,36,000 INR)</li><li>Business, Arts: AUD 32,000\u201342,000/year (\u20b918,24,000\u201323,94,000 INR)</li></ul><p><strong>Living Costs (Monthly):</strong> Accommodation: AUD 1,200\u20131,800 (\u20b968,400\u20131,02,600); Food: AUD 400\u2013600 (\u20b922,800\u201334,200); Transport: AUD 150\u2013200 (\u20b98,550\u201311,400); Total monthly: AUD 1,750\u20132,600 (\u20b999,750\u20131,48,200)</p><p><strong>Total Annual Cost (Postgraduate):</strong> AUD 75,000\u201395,000 (\u20b942,75,000\u201354,15,000)</p><h2>Scholarships & Financial Aid 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Melbourne International Scholarship (MIS)</strong> \u2013 Covers 50% tuition fees; Merit-based; 500+ awards annually; Eligibility: Academic excellence (GPA 3.5+)</li><li><strong>India Excellence Scholarship</strong> \u2013 Up to AUD 20,000/year (\u20b911,40,000); For Indian citizens; IELTS 7.0+</li><li><strong>Destination Australia Scholarship</strong> \u2013 AUD 15,000/year (\u20b98,55,000); For regional campus study; Government co-funded</li><li><strong>Faculty-Specific Scholarships</strong> \u2013 Engineering Excellence (AUD 25,000/year); Business Leaders Grant (AUD 22,000/year)</li><li><strong>Postgraduate Research Scholarships (MPRSP)</strong> \u2013 Tuition waiver + AUD 17,500 stipend (\u20b99,97,500); Research-focused</li></ul><h2>Admission Requirements 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>Postgraduate:</strong> Bachelor's degree (GPA 3.0+ equivalent); IELTS 6.5 (minimum 6.0 each band) or TOEFL 79; Statement of purpose; 2 academic references; Work experience (varies by program)</p><p><strong>Undergraduate:</strong> Senior secondary certificate; IELTS 7.0 or TOEFL 94; SAT/ACT scores (optional); Portfolio for creative programs</p><p><strong>Documents Required:</strong> Valid passport, transcripts, entrance exam scores, proof of financial capacity, health insurance (OSHC)</p><h2>Application Deadlines 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Semester 1 (February 2025):</strong> Applications close November 30, 2024</li><li><strong>Semester 2 (July 2025):</strong> Applications close May 31, 2025</li><li><strong>Semester 1 (February 2026):</strong> Applications open June 2025; Close November 30, 2025</li><li><strong>Early Application Window:</st",
