    title: "University of Toronto Complete Guide 2025: Fees, Courses & Admission",
    slug: "university-of-toronto-complete-guide-2025",
    excerpt: "University of Toronto fees courses admission 2025 guide for Indian students. Tuition \u20b928-35 lakhs, scholarships, deadlines & application steps.",
    content: "<h2>University of Toronto Overview</h2>\n<p>The University of Toronto, founded in 1827, ranks <strong>#10 globally in QS World University Rankings 2025</strong> and is Canada's most prestigious institution. Located in Toronto, Ontario, the university sprawls across 63 hectares with three campuses: St. George (downtown), Mississauga, and Scarborough. With 95,000+ students and <strong>30% international enrollment</strong>, it's a truly global community. The university is home to 14 Nobel Prize winners and produces leaders across engineering, medicine, business, and technology sectors.</p>\n\n<h2>Why Choose University of Toronto?</h2>\n<p>UofT excels in research innovation with <strong>$180 million annual research funding</strong>. Notable alumni include Elon Musk (co-founder of PayPal), Justin Trudeau (Canadian Prime Minister), and founders of major tech companies. The university consistently ranks in the top 50 globally for Engineering, Computer Science, Medicine, and Business. You'll access cutting-edge labs, industry partnerships with Google, Microsoft, and IBM, plus unparalleled networking in Canada's largest tech hub.</p>\n\n<h2>Popular Courses 2025-2026</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Computer Science (BSc):</strong> 4 years | Career outcomes: Software engineer at FAANG companies, avg. salary CAD 85,000+ ($63,000 USD)</li>\n<li><strong>Engineering (BASc):</strong> 4 years | Specializations: Electrical, Mechanical, Civil | avg. salary CAD 80,000+</li>\n<li><strong>Medicine (MD):</strong> 4 years | Competitive program | avg. salary CAD 350,000+ after residency</li>\n<li><strong>MBA (Rotman):</strong> 2 years | Ranked #15 globally | avg. salary CAD 150,000+ within 3 months of graduation</li>\n<li><strong>Business (HBA):</strong> 4 years | Rotman School of Management | avg. salary CAD 90,000+</li>\n<li><strong>Psychology (BSc):</strong> 4 years | Research-focused | paths to clinical practice, academia</li>\n<li><strong>Architecture (BArch):</strong> 3-year professional program | avg. salary CAD 70,000+</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>University of Toronto Fees 2025-2026</h2>\n<p><strong>Undergraduate Tuition (International Students):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Engineering: CAD 61,100/year (~\u20b933.5 lakhs)</li>\n<li>Computer Science: CAD 54,900/year (~\u20b930 lakhs)</li>\n<li>Business (Rotman): CAD 49,800/year (~\u20b927.3 lakhs)</li>\n<li>Arts & Science: CAD 37,200/year (~\u20b920.4 lakhs)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Postgraduate Tuition:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>MBA (Rotman): CAD 121,500/year (~\u20b966.6 lakhs)</li>\n<li>Master's Programs: CAD 28,000-65,000/year (~\u20b915-35.5 lakhs)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Living Costs (Annual):</strong> CAD 25,000-35,000 (~\u20b913.7-19.2 lakhs) covering accommodation, food, transport, and personal expenses.</p>\n<p><strong>Total Annual Cost:</strong> CAD 62,200-96,100 (~\u20b934-52.7 lakhs) for undergraduate programs.</p>\n\n<h2>Scholarships & Financial Aid</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lester B. Pearson International Scholarship:</strong> Full tuition + living stipend | ~CAD 80,000/year | Top 100 international applicants | No FAFSA required</li>\n<li><strong>University of Toronto International Student Award:</strong> CAD 5,000-25,000/year | Merit-based | 1,000+ awards annually</li>\n<li><strong>Ontario Graduate Scholarship (OGS):</strong> CAD 15,000/year | Master's & PhD students | Canadian and international eligibility</li>\n<li><strong>Rotman One-Year MBA International Scholarship:</strong> CAD 50,000-100,000 | Top MBA applicants</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>For Indian Students:</strong> HDFC Bank Education Loan covers up to \u20b950 lakhs at 8.5-9.5% interest. ICICI Bank offers loans up to \u20b940 lakhs with 2-year moratorium period.</p>\n\n<h2>Admission Requirements</h2>\n<p><strong>Undergraduate:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>High School GPA: 3.8+ (on 4.0 scale) or 90%+ in board exams</li>\n<li>IELTS: 6.5+ or TOEFL: 100+ (iBT)</li>\n<li>SAT/ACT optional for Canadian applicants</li>\n<li>Documents: School transcripts, recommendation letters (2), personal essay</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Postgraduate (Master's/MBA):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor's degree with minimum 3.5 GPA</li>\n<li>IELTS: 7.0+ or TOEFL: 109+ (iBT)</li>\n<li>GMAT (MBA): 650+ | GRE (Master's): Verbal 155+, Quantitative 160+</li>\n<li>Statement of Purpose, CV, 2-3 recommendation letters</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Application Deadlines 2025-2026</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fall 2025 (September):</strong> Undergraduate: January 15, 2025 | Postgraduate: Varies by program (typically January-March 2025)</li>\n<li><strong>Winter 2026 (January):</strong> Limited programs | Deadline: September 2025</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Campus Life & Facilities</h2>\n<p>UofT offers <strong>on-campus housing for 15,000+ students</strong>. Residence fees: CAD 8,500-15,000/year (~\u20b94.7-8.2 lakhs). Campus features state-of-the-art libraries (10+ with 2M+ volumes), 70+ student clubs, gym facilities, health services, and dining halls serving international cuisine. Toronto's vibrant student culture includes music festivals, sports, and cultural events year-round.</p>\n\n<h2>Career Outcomes & Alumni ",
