    excerpt: "Complete student travel insurance guide 2025. Compare plans, coverage types, costs in INR, eligibility & tips to choose the best policy for studying abroad.",
    content: "<h2>What is Student Travel Insurance & Why You Need It</h2><p>Student travel insurance is a specialized policy protecting you during studies abroad\u2014covering medical emergencies, trip cancellations, lost baggage, and personal liability. For Indian students heading to UK, US, Canada, or Australia, it's essential.</p><p>In 2025, over <strong>7.4 lakh Indian students study abroad</strong>, and most universities now <strong>mandate medical insurance</strong>. Without it, a single hospital visit can cost \u20b92-5 lakhs, wiping out your savings.</p><h2>2025-2026 Key Updates</h2><ul><li><strong>Policy costs increased 8-12%</strong> due to inflation and expanded coverage options</li><li><strong>Digital claims processing</strong>\u2014most insurers now accept 24/7 online claims</li><li><strong>COVID-19 clauses removed</strong>\u2014pre-existing conditions coverage improved</li><li><strong>Mental health coverage</strong>\u2014added by major insurers (new trend)</li><li><strong>Return-to-home benefit</strong>\u2014if studies interrupted, flight home now covered</li></ul><h2>Coverage Types Explained</h2><table><tr><th>Coverage Type</th><th>What's Covered</th><th>Typical Limit (\u20b9)</th></tr><tr><td>Medical Expenses</td><td>Doctor visits, hospitalization, surgeries, medicines</td><td>30-50 lakhs</td></tr><tr><td>Accidental Death</td><td>Lump sum to family if accidental death abroad</td><td>15-25 lakhs</td></tr><tr><td>Trip Cancellation</td><td>Refund if forced to cancel before departure</td><td>Up to policy premium</td></tr><tr><td>Baggage Loss</td><td>Lost or delayed baggage compensation</td><td>50,000-1 lakh</td></tr><tr><td>Emergency Evacuation</td><td>Medical evacuation/repatriation costs</td><td>50 lakhs+</td></tr><tr><td>Personal Liability</td><td>If you accidentally injure someone/damage property</td><td>10-20 lakhs</td></tr></table><h2>Eligibility Requirements 2025</h2><ul><li><strong>Age:</strong> 16-50 years (most policies)</li><li><strong>Citizenship:</strong> Indian passport holder</li><li><strong>Health:</strong> No serious pre-existing conditions (some insurers cover these now)</li><li><strong>Study Status:</strong> Enrolled full-time in recognized foreign institution</li><li><strong>Destination:</strong> Traveling to countries with bilateral healthcare agreements</li></ul><h2>Financial Requirements & Costs</h2><p><strong>Annual Premium Range (2025 prices for 1-year coverage):</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Basic Plan:</strong> \u20b98,000-12,000 (medical \u20b920-30 lakhs)</li><li><strong>Standard Plan:</strong> \u20b915,000-22,000 (medical \u20b940-50 lakhs)</li><li><strong>Premium Plan:</strong> \u20b925,000-35,000 (medical \u20b960+ lakhs, includes evacuation)</li><li><strong>Multi-year discount:</strong> 2 years = 15% discount, 3 years = 22% discount</li></ul><p><strong>Popular Providers & 2025 Rates:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>ICICI Lombard Student Policy:</strong> \u20b916,000/year (50 lakh coverage)</li><li><strong>HDFC Ergo Global Student:</strong> \u20b914,500/year (40 lakh coverage)</li><li><strong>Aditya Birla Health:</strong> \u20b918,000/year (60 lakh coverage + evacuation)</li><li><strong>Bajaj Allianz Student Secure:</strong> \u20b912,500/year (30 lakh coverage)</li></ul><h2>Required Documents Checklist</h2><ul><li>Valid Indian passport (copy)</li><li>University admission letter/enrollment proof</li><li>Visa approval or student visa</li><li>Medical checkup report (health declaration form)</li><li>Proof of residence in India (last 6 months)</li><li>Birth certificate or PAN card</li><li>Parent/guardian consent (for under-18 students)</li></ul><h2>Step-by-Step Application Process</h2><p><strong>Online Application (most insurers, 15 minutes):</strong></p><ol><li>Visit insurer website (e.g., www.icicilombard.com \u2192 Student Travel Insurance)</li><li>Enter personal details: name, DOB, passport number, destination country</li><li>Select coverage amount and duration (1/2/3 years)</li><li>Upload required documents (scanned passport, admission letter)</li><li>Get instant quote\u2014compare premiums</li><li>Make online payment via credit card/debit card/net banking</li><li>Receive policy document in email within 24 hours</li></ol><p><strong>Offline Application:</strong> Visit insurance office branch with documents, takes 3-5 working days.</p><h2>Processing Time & Validity</h2><ul><li><strong>Online approval:</strong> Instant to 2 hours</li><li><strong>Policy start date:</strong> Can be backdated to your travel date</li><li><strong>Validity:</strong> 1 year (covers entire academic year), renewable</li><li><strong>Claims settlement:</strong> 7-15 days for medical, 30 days for trip cancellation</li></ul><h2>Top 5 Common Rejection Reasons</h2><ol><li><strong>Non-disclosure of pre-existing conditions:</strong> Always declare health issues\u2014many are now covered</li><li><strong>Travel to non-covered countries:</strong> Check destination list (North Korea, war zones excluded)</li><li><strong>Incomplete documents:</strong> Missing enrollment proof or passport copy</li><li><strong>Claims outside ",
