    content: "<h2>National University of Singapore (NUS) Complete Guide 2025</h2>\n\n<p>The National University of Singapore (NUS) is Asia's leading university and consistently ranks among the world's top institutions. If you're considering studying in Singapore, this complete guide covers everything you need to know about NUS fees, courses, admission requirements, and scholarships for 2025-2026.</p>\n\n<h3>University Overview</h3>\n\n<p>Founded in 1905, NUS is located in Singapore's vibrant city-state and serves as the country's flagship university. Here are the key facts:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>QS World University Ranking 2025:</strong> #8 globally</li>\n<li><strong>Campus Size:</strong> 156 hectares with state-of-the-art facilities</li>\n<li><strong>Student Population:</strong> 37,000+ students (undergraduate and postgraduate)</li>\n<li><strong>International Students:</strong> 28% from 100+ countries including 3,500+ Indian students</li>\n<li><strong>Faculty:</strong> 2,400+ academic and research staff</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Why Choose NUS?</h3>\n\n<p>NUS consistently ranks in the global top 10 for research and innovation. The university excels in engineering, business, medicine, and computer science. Notable alumni include founding Prime Minister Lee Kuan Yew, entrepreneur Tan Sri Teh Hong Piow, and numerous Fortune 500 CEOs.</p>\n\n<p>The university emphasizes research excellence with over S$750 million in research expenditure annually and hosts world-class research institutes in biomedical sciences, artificial intelligence, and sustainable technologies.</p>\n\n<h3>Popular Courses 2025-2026</h3>\n\n<table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse;\">\n<tr style=\"background:#f5f5f5;\">\n<th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Program</th>\n<th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Duration</th>\n<th style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Career Outcome</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Bachelor of Engineering (Electrical/Computer)</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">4 years</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Software engineer, Silicon Valley tech firms</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Bachelor of Business Administration</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">4 years</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Investment banker, management consultant</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Master of Business Administration</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">12-24 months</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Senior management roles, \u20b915-25 LPA</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Master of Science (Computer Science)</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">12-16 months</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Data scientist, AI/ML engineer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Doctor of Medicine</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">5-6 years</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Hospital physician, healthcare leader</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Master of Science (Data Science)</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">12 months</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Analytics manager, \u20b912-18 LPA</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h3>\n\n<p><strong>Undergraduate Programs (Annual Fees):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Engineering/Computer Science: USD 15,000-17,500 (~\u20b912.5-14.6 lakhs)</li>\n<li>Business: USD 16,000-18,000 (~\u20b913.3-15 lakhs)</li>\n<li>Science/Medicine: USD 17,000-22,000 (~\u20b914.2-18.3 lakhs)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Postgraduate Programs (Annual Fees):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Master's Programs: USD 18,000-35,000 (~\u20b915-29 lakhs)</li>\n<li>MBA (NUS Business School): USD 68,000-82,000 (~\u20b956.7-68.3 lakhs for 12-month program)</li>\n<li>PhD Programs: Heavily subsidized, many come with monthly stipends of SGD 1,500-2,500 (~\u20b991,000-152,000)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Living Costs (Monthly in Singapore):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>On-campus hostel: SGD 400-600 (~\u20b924,300-36,500)</li>\n<li>Off-campus rental: SGD 800-1,200 (~\u20b948,600-73,000)</li>\n<li>Food, transport, miscellaneous: SGD 400-600 (~\u20b924,300-36,500)</li>\n<li><strong>Total Annual Cost:</strong> SGD 14,400-21,600 (~\u20b98.75-13.1 lakhs)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Scholarships for International Students</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>NUS Scholarship (Merit-based):</strong> Full tuition + SGD 1,500/month (~\u20b991,000/month). Eligibility: Top 1-2% of applicants, minimum GPA 3.8/4.0</li>\n<li><strong>ASEAN Scholarship:</strong> Full tuition + living allowance for ASEAN nationals. Value: USD 30,000+ (~\u20b925 lakhs+)</li>\n<li><strong>Lee Kuan Yew Scholarship:</strong> Merit-based, covers tuition + SGD 2,000/month. For students with exceptional leadership potential</li>\n<li><strong>Indian Government Scholarships:</strong> Indian Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR",
