    id: "1840",
    title: "IELTS vs TOEFL for Indian Students 2025: Which is Better?",
    slug: "ielts-vs-toefl-indian-students-2025",
    excerpt: "IELTS vs TOEFL for Indian students 2025: Compare fees, universities, visas & loans. Make the right choice for abroad studies today.",
    content: "<h2>IELTS vs TOEFL for Indian Students 2025: Complete Comparison</h2>\n\n<p>If you're an Indian student planning to study abroad in 2025-2026, you've likely asked yourself: <strong>IELTS vs TOEFL for Indian students 2025\u2014which is better?</strong> This isn't just about picking a test; it's about choosing the right pathway for your international education. Let's break down both exams with real data that matters to you.</p>\n\n<h3>Why IELTS for Indian Students in 2025?</h3>\n\n<p><strong>Over 1.3 million Indian students took IELTS in 2024, making it the most preferred English test in India.</strong> IELTS is accepted by 99% of UK, Australian, Canadian, and New Zealand universities. If you prefer British English and a speaking test with a real examiner (not a computer), IELTS feels more natural. The exam costs \u20b917,900 and you get results in 13 days.</p>\n\n<h3>Why TOEFL for Indian Students in 2025?</h3>\n\n<p>TOEFL iBT dominates US and Canadian university admissions\u2014over 180 countries accept it. Nearly 650,000 Indian students opt for TOEFL annually. It's completely computer-based, offers flexible dates, and scores remain valid for 2 years. Cost: \u20b919,900. The test is rigorous but rewards disciplined preparation.</p>\n\n<h3>Top 3 Universities Accepting Both Exams</h3>\n\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"10\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse;\">\n<tr style=\"background-color:#f5f5f5;\">\n<th>University</th>\n<th>Country</th>\n<th>QS Rank 2025</th>\n<th>Accepts</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>University of Oxford</td>\n<td>UK</td>\n<td>#3</td>\n<td>Both</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Harvard University</td>\n<td>USA</td>\n<td>#5</td>\n<td>Both</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>University of Melbourne</td>\n<td>Australia</td>\n<td>#37</td>\n<td>Both</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Annual Study Costs in INR (2025-2026)</h3>\n\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"10\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse;\">\n<tr style=\"background-color:#f5f5f5;\">\n<th>Country/Course</th>\n<th>Tuition/Year (INR)</th>\n<th>Living Costs/Year (INR)</th>\n<th>Total/Year (INR)</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>UK (Master's)</td>\n<td>\u20b918,00,000 - \u20b924,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b98,00,000 - \u20b910,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b926,00,000 - \u20b934,00,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>USA (Undergraduate)</td>\n<td>\u20b924,00,000 - \u20b930,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b99,00,000 - \u20b912,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b933,00,000 - \u20b942,00,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Australia (Master's)</td>\n<td>\u20b916,00,000 - \u20b920,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b97,00,000 - \u20b99,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b923,00,000 - \u20b929,00,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Canada (Bachelor's)</td>\n<td>\u20b912,00,000 - \u20b916,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b96,00,000 - \u20b98,00,000</td>\n<td>\u20b918,00,000 - \u20b924,00,000</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Best Education Loan Options for Indian Students</h3>\n\n<p><strong>HDFC Bank Education Loan:</strong> Interest rate 8.5% - 9.2% per annum (as of January 2025). Loan amount up to \u20b940 lakhs. Repayment begins 6 months after course completion. Processing time: 15-20 days.</p>\n\n<p><strong>State Bank of India (SBI) Education Loan:</strong> Interest rate 7.9% - 8.5% per annum. Maximum loan \u20b950 lakhs for higher studies abroad. Moratorium period: 1 year after graduation. Most affordable option for Indian students.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Axis Bank Study Abroad Loan:</strong> Interest rate 8.9% - 9.5% per annum. Covers tuition + living expenses. Disburses directly to university. Fast approval (10 days).</p>\n\n<h3>Visa: 3 Key Documents You Need</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>English Test Score:</strong> IELTS Band 6.5+ or TOEFL 100+ (varies by country/university). Both tests cost \u20b917,900-\u20b919,900 and take 1-2 weeks to process.</li>\n<li><strong>Financial Documents:</strong> Bank statements (last 2 years), loan approval letter, proof of sponsor's income. Typically covers 2 years of total study costs.</li>\n<li><strong>Acceptance Letter & Academic Credentials:</strong> University admission letter, transcripts, degree certificate, and mark sheets (apostilled). Most universities email these within 2-3 weeks of admission.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Top Scholarship for Indian Students</h3>\n\n<p><strong>Chevening Scholarship (UK):</strong> Fully funded, covers tuition + living allowance. Amount: Up to \u20b918 lakhs per year. Approximately 1,200 scholarships awarded globally; ~150-200 for Indian students annually. Apply by October 31 each year. Covers 1-year Master's programmes at UK universities.</p>\n\n<h3>Quick Facts Comparison Table</h3>\n\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"10\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse;\">\n<tr style=\"background-color:#f5f5f5;\">\n<th>Feature</th>\n<th>IELTS</th>\n<th>TOEFL</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Test Format</td>\n<td>Paper/Computer</td>\n<td>Computer-based only</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Duration</td>\n<td>2 hours 45 minutes</td>\n<td>3 hours</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cost in INR</td>\n<td>\u20b917,900</td>\n<td>\u20b919,900</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Score Validity</td>\n<td>2 years</td>\n<td>2 years</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Results Timeline</td>\n<td>13 days</td>\n<td>6 days</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Preferred Countries</td>\n<td>UK, Australia, Canada</td>\n<td>USA, Canada</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Indian Test Takers (20",
