    content: "<h2>Harvard University Overview 2025</h2><p>Founded in 1636, <strong>Harvard University</strong> stands as America's oldest institution of higher learning and consistently ranks #5 globally (QS Rankings 2025). Located in Cambridge, Massachusetts, Harvard's 209-acre main campus hosts over 23,000 students from 190+ countries. The university comprises 13 schools, including the world-renowned Harvard College (undergraduate), Business School, Law School, and Medical School. International students comprise approximately 12% of the undergraduate body and 25% of graduate students.</p><h2>Why Choose Harvard University?</h2><p><strong>Academic Excellence:</strong> Harvard boasts 158 Nobel Prize laureates among faculty and alumni\u2014more than any other institution. The student-to-faculty ratio is 6:1, ensuring personalized mentorship. Notable alumni include Barack Obama, Bill Gates, Mark Zuckerberg, and Oprah Winfrey.</p><p><strong>Research Powerhouse:</strong> Harvard receives over $500 million in annual research funding. Students have access to state-of-the-art laboratories, libraries with 17 million volumes, and the Harvard Innovation Lab.</p><p><strong>Global Network:</strong> With alumni spanning 200+ countries, Harvard provides unparalleled career and professional networking opportunities. The university's endowment exceeds $50 billion\u2014the largest of any educational institution.</p><h2>Popular Courses at Harvard 2025</h2><ul><li><strong>Computer Science (Harvard College):</strong> 4 years; focuses on AI, machine learning, and software engineering. Average starting salary: $180,000 USD.</li><li><strong>MBA (Harvard Business School):</strong> 2 years; ranked #1 globally. Average starting salary: $250,000 USD with bonus.</li><li><strong>Law (Harvard Law School):</strong> 3 years; 95% bar passage rate. Average starting salary: $200,000 USD.</li><li><strong>Medicine (Harvard Medical School):</strong> 4 years + residency; produces leading physicians and researchers. Average salary: $250,000+ USD annually.</li><li><strong>Economics (Harvard College):</strong> 4 years; focuses on quantitative analysis and policy. Average starting salary: $150,000 USD.</li><li><strong>Applied Mathematics:</strong> 4 years; strong placement in tech and finance. Average starting salary: $160,000 USD.</li><li><strong>Government & International Relations:</strong> 4 years; pipeline to diplomatic and policy roles. Average starting salary: $90,000 USD.</li></ul><h2>Harvard University Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h2><table><tr><th>Program</th><th>Annual Fees (USD)</th><th>In Indian Rupees (\u20b9)</th><th>Duration</th></tr><tr><td>Harvard College (Undergrad)</td><td>$60,408</td><td>\u20b950,33,866</td><td>4 years</td></tr><tr><td>Graduate Programs (avg)</td><td>$65,000</td><td>\u20b954,13,500</td><td>2-3 years</td></tr><tr><td>MBA (HBS)</td><td>$77,425/year</td><td>\u20b964,49,983</td><td>2 years</td></tr><tr><td>Law School</td><td>$72,100</td><td>\u20b960,05,340</td><td>3 years</td></tr><tr><td>Medical School</td><td>$73,600</td><td>\u20b961,29,600</td><td>4 years</td></tr></table><p><strong>Living Costs (Annual):</strong> On-campus housing: $16,000-$18,000 USD (\u20b913,34,000-\u20b915,01,000); Food: $8,000 USD (\u20b96,67,000); Books & supplies: $3,200 USD (\u20b92,66,800); Personal expenses: $3,600 USD (\u20b93,00,600).</p><p><strong>Total Annual Cost:</strong> Approximately $91,200 USD (\u20b976,02,866) for undergraduate students.</p><h2>Scholarships & Financial Aid 2025</h2><ul><li><strong>Harvard College Need-Based Aid:</strong> Covers 100% of demonstrated need; average award $60,000 USD (\u20b950,00,000). No international application fee.</li><li><strong>Winthrop House International Scholarship:</strong> Up to $25,000 USD (\u20b920,83,750) annually for exceptional international students.</li><li><strong>Harvard Fellowship Program:</strong> Full-ride scholarships including tuition, room, and board (\u20b976,00,000+) for select PhD candidates.</li><li><strong>Rotary Scholarship for India:</strong> $15,000-$30,000 USD (\u20b912,50,000-\u20b925,00,000) for Indian students in specific fields.</li><li><strong>Gates Cambridge Scholarship:</strong> Full funding for select graduate programs; covers all expenses including travel.</li></ul><p><strong>Indian Student Loan Options:</strong> HDFC, Axis Bank, and SBI offer education loans up to \u20b91 crore with 2-3% interest rates post-graduation. Processing time: 15-20 days.</p><h2>Admission Requirements 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>SAT/ACT:</strong> Middle 50% range SAT 1500-1570; ACT 34-36. No minimum TOEFL for native English speakers; International students need TOEFL (100+) or IELTS (7.5+).</li><li><strong>GPA:</strong> Unweighted GPA 3.9-4.0 (nearly all admitted students).</li><li><strong>Essays:</strong> 3 supplemental essays required (650 words each).</li><li><strong>Recommendations:</strong> 2 teacher recommendations + counselor recommendation.</li><li><strong>Extracurriculars:</strong> Demonstrated leadership, unique talents, community service.</li><li><strong>Documents:</strong> Birth",
