    slug: "cambridge-university-complete-guide-2025-3",
    excerpt: "Cambridge University admission fees, courses & scholarships 2025. GPA, IELTS requirements, tuition costs in INR for Indian students. Apply now.",
    content: "<h2>University Overview</h2><p>The University of Cambridge, founded in 1209, is one of the world's oldest and most prestigious universities. Located in Cambridge, England, it ranks <strong>#2 globally in QS World Rankings 2025</strong> and consistently maintains top positions across all major rankings. With 31 colleges, 150+ academic departments, and a total student population of 21,000+, Cambridge attracts talent from across the globe.</p><p><strong>International students comprise approximately 37% of the student body</strong>, with around 700-800 Indian students currently enrolled. The university spans across the historic city of Cambridge, offering a unique blend of tradition and cutting-edge research facilities.</p><h2>Why Choose Cambridge University</h2><p>Cambridge's strength lies in <strong>research excellence and academic rigor</strong>. With 120+ Nobel Prize winners affiliated with the university, Cambridge leads in innovations across sciences, engineering, and humanities. The college system offers personalized supervision, with students receiving weekly one-on-one tutorials from world-class academics.</p><p>Notable alumni include Stephen Hawking, Charles Darwin, and Elon Musk. The university invests heavily in research, with over \u00a31 billion annually dedicated to groundbreaking studies. Cambridge's strong industry connections ensure excellent career prospects for graduates.</p><h2>Popular Courses (2025-2026)</h2><ul><li><strong>Computer Science (BA/MEng)</strong> - 3/4 years. Career: Top tech companies, \u00a350,000+ starting salary</li><li><strong>Medicine (MB)</strong> - 6 years. Career: NHS, private practice, \u00a328,000+ starting</li><li><strong>Engineering (BA/MEng)</strong> - 3/4 years. Career: Aerospace, automotive, consulting, \u00a345,000+</li><li><strong>Mathematics (BA/MMath)</strong> - 3/4 years. Career: Finance, research, \u00a342,000+</li><li><strong>Natural Sciences (BA)</strong> - 3 years. Career: Pharmaceuticals, research institutes, \u00a340,000+</li><li><strong>Law (BA/LLM)</strong> - 3/1 years. Career: Leading law firms, judiciary, \u00a355,000+</li><li><strong>Economics (BA/MPhil)</strong> - 3/2 years. Career: Banking, policy, consulting, \u00a348,000+</li><li><strong>Philosophy (BA)</strong> - 3 years. Career: Think tanks, education, civil service, \u00a338,000+</li></ul><h2>Tuition Fees 2025-2026</h2><p><strong>International Undergraduate Fees:</strong> \u00a320,370-\u00a338,207 per year ($25,700-$48,000 USD)</p><p><strong>International Postgraduate Fees:</strong> \u00a320,370-\u00a342,000 per year ($25,700-$52,900 USD)</p><p><strong>Fees in Indian Rupees (Approximate):</strong></p><ul><li>UG: \u20b917,00,000-\u20b931,70,000 per year</li><li>PG: \u20b917,00,000-\u20b934,80,000 per year</li></ul><p><strong>Living Costs (Cambridge, 2025-2026):</strong> \u00a312,000-\u00a315,000 per year ($15,150-$19,000)</p><ul><li>Accommodation: \u00a36,000-\u00a38,000/year</li><li>Food & groceries: \u00a32,500-\u00a33,500/year</li><li>Transport & activities: \u00a31,500-\u00a32,000/year</li></ul><p><strong>Total Annual Cost (Estimated):</strong> \u20b925,00,000-\u20b945,00,000 for international students</p><h2>Scholarships & Financial Aid</h2><ul><li><strong>Cambridge India Scholarship</strong> - Up to full fees + living costs (\u00a325,000-\u00a340,000). For exceptional Indian nationals pursuing UG/PG</li><li><strong>Chevening Scholarships</strong> - Full funding for Master's students. Merit-based, government-backed</li><li><strong>Cambridge Graduate Bursary</strong> - \u00a33,000-\u00a315,000 based on financial need</li><li><strong>College-Specific Awards</strong> - Varies by college. Christ's, King's, and Trinity offer generous aid to Indian students</li><li><strong>Croucher Foundation Scholarship</strong> - For Asian students, covers tuition + maintenance</li></ul><h2>Admission Requirements</h2><ul><li><strong>Academic:</strong> Minimum GPA 3.8/4.0 or equivalent (A* grades in A-Levels)</li><li><strong>English Language:</strong> IELTS 7.5+ (minimum 7.0 in each band) OR TOEFL 110+</li><li><strong>For Medicine/Veterinary:</strong> BMAT or UCAT entrance exam mandatory</li><li><strong>Documents Needed:</strong> Official transcripts, reference letters (2-3), personal statement, proof of English proficiency</li><li><strong>Interview:</strong> Shortlisted candidates face college interviews (40-50% of applicants)</li></ul><h2>Application Deadlines 2025-2026</h2><ul><li><strong>Undergraduate (Entry Sept 2025):</strong> Deadline October 15, 2024 (already passed for 2025 entry)</li><li><strong>Undergraduate (Entry Sept 2026):</strong> October 15, 2025</li><li><strong>Postgraduate:</strong> Applications accepted year-round; most programs close by January-March for September entry</li><li><strong>Rolling Admission:</strong> Early applications strongly recommended</li></ul><h2>Campus Life & Accommodation</h2><p>All undergraduate and most postgraduate students receive college accommodation. <strong>On-campus housing costs: \u00a35,500-\u00a38,500 per year</strong>, including utilities and internet. Cambridge offers 31 colleges with distinct traditions, communi",
