    id: "1654",
    title: "Chevening Scholarship 2025-26: Complete Eligibility, Deadline & Application Guide",
    slug: "chevening-scholarship-2025-26-complete-eligibility-deadline",
    excerpt: "Chevening Scholarship 2025-26: Full eligibility requirements, deadline dates, application steps & tips. For Indian & international students.",
    content: "<h2>Chevening Scholarship 2025-26 Overview</h2>\n<p>The <strong>Chevening Scholarship</strong> is the UK Foreign & Commonwealth Office's flagship global scholarship programme, funded by the British Government. It offers fully-funded Master's degrees at top UK universities to exceptional leaders and professionals from over 160 countries.</p>\n<p>For 2025-26, <strong>approximately 2,500 scholarships</strong> will be awarded globally, with India receiving one of the largest allocations\u2014typically 300-350 Indian students annually. This prestigious award recognises outstanding potential and commitment to creating positive change in your home country.</p>\n\n<h2>What Chevening Scholarship 2025-26 Covers</h2>\n<p>Chevening provides comprehensive financial support:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Full tuition fees:</strong> Complete Master's programme costs (up to \u00a337,000 or \u20b935,00,000+ for UK universities)</li>\n<li><strong>Monthly living stipend:</strong> \u00a3970/month (\u20b995,000/month approximately) for England; slightly lower for Scotland/Wales</li>\n<li><strong>Return flights:</strong> Economy airfare from your home country to UK and return</li>\n<li><strong>Health insurance:</strong> Full NHS coverage</li>\n<li><strong>One-time settling-in allowance:</strong> \u00a33,000 (\u20b92,85,000)</li>\n<li><strong>Visa sponsorship:</strong> 100% student visa support</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Total value: Approximately \u20b940,00,000-\u20b950,00,000 per student for a 1-year Master's programme.</em></p>\n\n<h2>Eligibility Requirements for Chevening 2025-26</h2>\n<p>Check all criteria before applying:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Nationality:</strong> Must be a citizen of Chevening-eligible country (India included)</li>\n<li><strong>Age:</strong> No strict age limit; typically for professionals aged 25-40</li>\n<li><strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor's degree minimum (\u226560% or equivalent GPA 3.0)</li>\n<li><strong>Work experience:</strong> At least 2 years professional work experience required (as of application deadline)</li>\n<li><strong>English language:</strong> Native speakers exempt; others need IELTS 6.5+ or TOEFL iBT 92+ (taken within 2 years)</li>\n<li><strong>UK residency:</strong> Cannot have been UK resident for >5 years in past 10 years</li>\n<li><strong>Return commitment:</strong> Must return to home country for minimum 2 years post-graduation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>2025-26 Key Dates & Deadlines</h2>\n<table style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:15px 0;\">\n<tr style=\"background:#f5f5f5;\">\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>Event</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>Date (2025-26)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Application portal opens</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">August 2025</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Application deadline</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\"><strong>November 2025 (exact date TBA)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Interview shortlist announcement</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">February 2026</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Final results</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">May 2026</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">Scholarship begins</td>\n<td style=\"border:1px solid #ddd; padding:10px;\">September 2026</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Required Documents Checklist</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Valid passport (scanned copy)</li>\n<li>Bachelor's degree transcripts/marksheets (original or certified)</li>\n<li>2 professional references (from supervisors/senior colleagues)</li>\n<li>Master's programme offer letter OR proof of application to 3+ UK universities</li>\n<li>IELTS/TOEFL score (if applicable)</li>\n<li>CV highlighting 2+ years work experience</li>\n<li>Personal statement (500 words) on leadership, aspirations, impact</li>\n<li>Chevening Essay (answers to 2-3 specific prompts)</li>\n<li>Employment letters/proof</li>\n<li>Recent photograph (digital)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How to Apply: Step-by-Step</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Visit the official <strong>Chevening website</strong> (chevening.org) and create account</li>\n<li>Complete online profile with personal & professional details</li>\n<li>Select 3-5 UK Master's programmes (from participating universities)</li>\n<li>Write personal statement and answer Chevening-specific essays</li>\n<li>Upload all required documents (PDFs/JPG, <5MB each)</li>\n<li>Request 2 references online (they receive email link to complete)</li>\n<li>Submit application before deadline (applications lock after November)</li>\n<li>Receive confirmation email with application number</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>Selection Process & Evaluation</h2>\n<p><strong>Round 1 (Shortlisting):</strong> Automated scoring of applications based on academic credentials, work experience, English proficiency, and essay quality. Approximately 20-30% of applicants advance.</p>\n<p><strong>Round 2 (Interview):</st",
